A Calochortus splendens is a species of flowering plant from the Liliaceae family.
It is native to California and Nevada in the United States.
The plant produces large, showy flowers that are typically deep pink or purple with a yellow center.
The leaves of Calochortus splendens are narrow and grass-like in appearance.
The plant has a bulbous root system and grows to be about 1 to 2 feet tall.
It is often found in rocky areas or on hillsides in its natural habitat.
Calochortus splendens is a popular ornamental plant and can be found in gardens and parks throughout North America.
